Repost from @kikiekaa
#KIKAtravelreview
'When the beast meets the beauty'
A picture that reflect the exotic of Baluran National Park which I currently describe as Africa van Java.
.
It was my first experience to explore the beautiful North Banyuwangi in East Java.
.
At first, it was just like an ordinary forest, but after 30 minutes ride throughout the forest, we'll see an exotic plant and wildlife diversity. 
From peacocks and many herd of deer that running freely in the wild, many soaring eagles in the sky, and many wild buffaloes welcoming us with curiosity in the savana.
.
Beside the forest, savana and the wildlife that we can explore and enjoy, there's a snorkling spot called Bama Beach as well.
.
Basically, Baluran National Park is a perfect combination of a thick wild natural rain forest, a great mountain view, a vast savana, an underwater coral park, white beach sands and an amazing wildlife, all packed in one great journey at once.
‚Ä¢
‚Ä¢
Indonesia is really amazing, it provides you many great, amazing and exotic destination.. all you have to do is just step out, travel and explore it.
Location : Savana Bekol, Taman Nasional Baluran - Banyuwangi
In Frame : @aulia.harrits 
Captured by @kikiekaa
